    waterUtilityPara: "NYC Department of Environmental Protection (DEP) draws water from the Catskill, Delaware, and Croton watersheds through a gravity-fed tunnel system without filtration. The system delivers some of the softest municipal water in the country at 15 to 30 ppm hardness measured at Kensico Reservoir. DEP maintains the main to the curb stop; the service line from the curb stop to the building is homeowner-responsible. The 2008 Filtration Avoidance Determination renewal and ongoing Water Supply Permit revisions through the Catskill Filtration Avoidance process shape long-term supply policy.",
